metadata.description: Cerebral artery branches processed from DOI 10.3171/jns.1978.49.2.0204 and Wikipedia references

entries.label: inferior parietal artery
entries.definition: An artery that branches from the middle cerebral artery and supplies the inferior parietal cortex.
entries.creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

entries.label: medial lenticulostriate artery
entries.definition: An artery that branches from the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the striatum.
entries.creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

entries.label: middle internal frontal artery
entries.definition: An artery that branches from the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the middle portion of the frontal lobe on the medial surface.
entries.creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

entries.label: orbitofrontal branch of anterior cerebral artery
entries.definition: An artery that branches from the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the medial orbital frontal cortex.
entries.creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

entries.label: orbitofrontal branch of middle cerebral artery
entries.definition: An artery that branches from the middle cerebral artery and supplies the lateral orbital frontal cortex.
entries.creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

entries.label: paracentral artery
entries.definition: An artery that branches from the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the paracentral lobule.
entries.creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

entries.label: posterior internal frontal artery
entries.definition: An artery that branches from the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the posterior portion of the frontal lobe on the medial surface.
entries.creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

entries.label: superior parietal artery
entries.definition: An artery that branches from the middle cerebral artery and supplies the superior parietal cortex.
entries.creator: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489

79.label: inferior parietal artery
79.reference: DOI:10.3171/jns.1978.49.2.0204 - Neurosurgery paper on cerebral artery anatomy
79.justification: The inferior parietal artery is a cortical branch of the middle cerebral artery that supplies the inferior parietal lobule/cortex. From the referenced neurosurgery literature on cerebral artery anatomy, this artery is part of the cortical branching pattern of the MCA supplying the parietal lobe regions.

111.label: medial lenticulostriate artery
111.justification: The medial lenticulostriate arteries (also known as recurrent artery of Heubner) branch from the anterior cerebral artery and supply the striatum (caudate nucleus and putamen). These are small perforating arteries that arise from the A1 segment and/or proximal A2 segment of the ACA.

120.label: middle internal frontal artery
120.reference: DOI:10.3171/jns.1978.49.2.0204 - Neurosurgery paper on cerebral artery anatomy
120.justification: The middle internal frontal artery is one of the cortical branches of the anterior cerebral artery that supplies the medial surface of the frontal lobe. This vessel is part of the systematic cortical branching pattern of the ACA described in the neurosurgical literature.

122.label: orbitofrontal branch of anterior cerebral artery
122.justification: The orbitofrontal artery branches from the A2 segment of the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the medial orbital frontal cortex. This artery courses anteriorly to supply the orbital and medial frontal regions.

123.label: orbitofrontal branch of middle cerebral artery
123.justification: The orbitofrontal artery can arise from the middle cerebral artery (M2 segment) and supplies portions of the orbital frontal cortex. While the ACA typically supplies medial orbital regions, the MCA can contribute to lateral orbital regions.

124.label: paracentral artery
124.reference: DOI:10.3171/jns.1978.49.2.0204 - Neurosurgery paper on cerebral artery anatomy
124.justification: The paracentral artery is a medial cortical branch of the anterior cerebral artery that supplies the paracentral lobule, which includes portions of the primary motor and sensory cortex on the medial surface of the hemisphere. This region straddles the central sulcus on the medial aspect.

128.label: posterior internal frontal artery
128.reference: DOI:10.3171/jns.1978.49.2.0204 - Neurosurgery paper on cerebral artery anatomy
128.justification: The posterior internal frontal artery is a cortical branch of the anterior cerebral artery supplying the posterior medial frontal lobe. This is part of the systematic cortical distribution pattern of the ACA along the medial hemispheric surface.

157.label: superior parietal artery
157.reference: DOI:10.3171/jns.1978.49.2.0204 - Neurosurgery paper on cerebral artery anatomy
157.justification: The superior parietal artery is a cortical branch of the middle cerebral artery that supplies the superior parietal lobule/cortex. This artery is part of the posterior cortical branches of the MCA that supply the parietal lobe regions.
